Most Relevant Clusters: In each interaction round, the index of representatives is used to identify, for each modality, the b clusters most likely to contain useful candidates for suggestions. This search expansion parameter, b, affects the size of the subset that will be scored and can be used to balance between search quality and latency at run-time. All cluster representatives are scored by the interactive classifier and the b clusters farthest from the separating plane in the positive direction are selected as the most relevant clusters. In Sect. 4.3 we evaluate the effects of b on the YFCC100M collection.

