Most Relevant Suggestions: Once the r most relevant candidates from each modality have been identified, the modalities must be fused by aggregating the candidate lists to produce the final list of k suggestions. First, for each candidate in one modality, the score in the other modality is computed if necessary, by directly accessing the compressed feature vector, resulting in 2r candidates with scores in both modalities.2 Second, the rank of each item in each modality is computed by sorting the 2r candidates. Finally, the average rank is used to produce the final list of suggestions.

